name: Four Suns, Four Symmetrees, Eight Scrub-Jays in Light, Eight Scrub-Jays in Mist, Single Coastal Redwood
description: I made this painting in Ashland, Oregon during the 2020 wildfire season. There was one week, while living with Julia Yerger and Jeffrey Alan Scudder, that we weren't able to leave the house due to air quality concerns: Ashland was measuring over 400 on the Air Quality Index of AirNow.gov. We were painting on our computers and on Jeffrey's iPad. That was the week I made this painting.
